    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-11-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-11-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="141"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d141">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No 893.00/672.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-11-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 17, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The immediate question confronting Yuan Shih Kai is money for current expenses.
                    Brigandage is increasing throughout the country and business is suspended; the
                    approach of winter increases the gravity of the situation. Local banking
                    representatives of the four groups seem willing to make a loan if actively
                    supported by their Governments. A further question arises as to whether the loan
                    if made should include only the four groups or all foreign interests. And the
                    delicate international question also enters as to who shall take the initiative.
                    Please instruct.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Calhoun</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
